Tunisia who reported that their SIM cards were broken and phones taken away by Government forces 
at checkpoints to conceal evidence they may possess. 
</p>
<p> 95 On 30 March 2011, Libyan authorities expelled, without justification, Michael Georgy, a Reuter&#8223;s 
correspondent who had been covering the conflict since 28 February. See Reuters, &#8220;Libyan 
